             was indicted for that he, on the <rs id="t17950520-29-cd164" type="crimeDate">13th of April</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950520-29-off165 t17950520-29-cd164"></join>, feloniously did <rs id="t17950520-29-off165" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950520-29-off165" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950520-29-off165" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               falsely make, forge and counterfeit, and did cause and procure to be falsely made, forged, and counterfeited; and did willingly act and assist in the false making, forging, and counterfeiting a certain order for payment of money, dated Chelmsford, 11th of April 1795, with the name of 
                     <persName id="t17950520-29-person362">
                        Edward
                         Gepp
                     <interp inst="t17950520-29-person362" type="surname" value="Gepp"></interp>
